{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-configure-wishlist-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Configure Wishlist in Magento 2?","content":"\n<p>It&#8217;s common for customers to need some time to consider their options before making a purchase while shopping. While you can provide features such as recently viewed or compared products, having a wishlist on your Magento 2 store can be extremely beneficial. A wishlist allows customers to add items they are interested in to a personalized list, making it easy for them to come back and make a purchase at a later time. This feature also allows customers to share their wishlists with friends, potentially increasing the demand for your products and expanding your customer base. As a store owner, knowing <strong><em>how to configure wishlist in Magento 2</em></strong> is essential for effectively setting up and managing wishlists on your online store.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How to Configure Wishlist in Magento 2: A Step-by-Step Guide for Store Owners</strong></h1>\n\n\n\n<p>there are specific steps that store owners must follow to ensure that the feature is set up correctly and effectively.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is a Wishlist in Magento?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most useful features of Magento 2 is the ability for registered customers to create wishlists. Wishlists allow customers to collect products they are interested in but haven&#8217;t yet purchased, which can be saved for future visits or shared with friends. However, it&#8217;s not only beneficial for customers; store owners can also benefit from wishlists.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By configuring wishlists in Magento 2, store owners can gain valuable insights into their sales trends and customer behavior. By analyzing the data from wishlists, they can determine which products are popular and which items customers are saving for later. This information can help store owners adjust their pricing and tailor their product page content to specific customer groups. For example, they can offer promotions for products that are frequently saved in wishlists to encourage customers to make a purchase.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, by promoting the use of wishlists on their website, store owners can increase customer engagement and loyalty. Customers will appreciate the convenience of being able to save products they are interested in, which can lead to repeat visits and purchases.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, <strong><em>configure wishlists in Magento 2</em></strong> can be an invaluable tool for store owners to better understand their customers&#8217; preferences, adjust their sales strategies, and ultimately drive sales and customer loyalty.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How Wishlist Function in Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you enable wishlists in your Magento 2 store, a new &#8220;Add to Wishlist&#8221; button appears on product and category pages. Customers can click this button to add the product to their wishlist. From there, they can modify the quantity of the item, leave comments, and even share the list with others via email using the store email address. Customers also have the option to include a message when sharing their wishlist, although this is not required.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To offer your customers more options and increase the likelihood of purchase, you can create bundle products in Magento 2. Bundle products allow customers to purchase multiple products together as a bundle, often at a discounted price. This can be an effective way to increase sales and customer satisfaction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re interested in creating bundle products in Magento 2, our guide on <a href=\"/how-to-create-bundle-product-in-magento-2/\">How to Create Bundle Product in Magento 2</a> can help. This guide provides step-by-step instructions on how to create bundle products in your store, including how to add products to the bundle, set the price and discount, and customize the product page display.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, wishlists and bundle products are powerful features of Magento 2 that can help you improve customer engagement, increase sales, and drive business growth. By configuring these features correctly and promoting them effectively, you can create a more user-friendly and satisfying shopping experience for your customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on <strong><em>how to configure wishlists in Magento 2</em></strong>, keep reading.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Configure Wishlist in Magento 2?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To configure wishlists in Magento 2:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1.Navigate to Stores &gt; Settings &gt; Configuration &gt; Customers &gt; Wish List.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1455 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:363px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;545&#x27;%20width=&#x27;363&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 363px) 363px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/fac45d31f729453d8394bf40ac675e11/52dad2a13bf16731e58abdaa21868a5a/How-to-Configure-Wishlist-in-Magento-2-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%