x) 832px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":832,\"height\":591},\"alt\":\"How to Configure Wishlist in Magento 2 03\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1457 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"3\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Select the Email Sender, which defines the name that will appear in the emails.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose the <a href=\"https://devdocs.magento.com/guides/v2.3/frontend-dev-guide/templates/template-email.html\">Email Template</a> used when customers share their wishlists. (Note: The Wish List Sharing template is set by default, but you can customize email templates and use your own.)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Set the Max Emails Allowed to be Sent (default is 10, with a maximum of 10000).</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Define the Email Text Length Limit (can vary from 250 to 10000).</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Set Display Wish List Summary in the My Wish List Link section to either display the number of items in the wishlist or item quantities.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to press the Save Config button after you&#8217;ve completed these steps. Once you have configured the wishlists, you can learn how to share them.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Magento 2 Share Wishlist?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sharing a wishlist in Magento 2 is a straightforward process, making it easy for your customers to share their wishlists with family and friends.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Share a Wishlist:</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Go to the My Wish List section and press the Share Wish List button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Enter the email addresses to which the wishlist will be sent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Add a Message for the receivers (optional).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Press the Share Wish List button to send the wishlist.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this simple process, you have successfully configured Magento 2 wishlists and learned how to share them. This feature will make your store more customer-friendly and help retain customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For an even higher likelihood of a purchase, consider adding related products to the shopping cart page, offering customers more options in case they&#8217;re uncertain about the product.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To conclude, generating and configuring wishlists in Magento 2 is a valuable and straightforward process. By enabling this feature, customers can easily save and share their favorite items, while store owners gain valuable insight into customer behavior and preferences. Integrating wishlists into your store&#8217;s strategy can lead to increased customer satisfaction and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started with wishlists in Magento 2, it&#8217;s important to customize the email templates, set limits on the number of emails that can be sent, and display wishlist summaries according to your store&#8217;s needs. Our guide on <strong><em>How to Configure Wishlist in Magento 2</em></strong> provides step-by-step instructions on how to set up and manage wishlists in your store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once your wishlists are up and running, you can analyze the data they provide to better understand your customers and optimize your sales strategy. For example, you may discover that certain products are frequently saved to wishlists but not often purchased. This information can help you adjust your pricing or marketing approach to better align with customer preferences.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In short, <strong><em>generate wishlist in Magento 2</em></strong> is a powerful tool that can help you grow your business and improve customer satisfaction. By following the best practices outlined in our guide, you can easily implement this feature in your store and start reaping the benefits.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div c